0.name: Floating in a twisted, multi-coloured vortex.
desc: "   You tumble and drift slowly in this weightless environment.  Everywhere
you turn, coloured twisting light and magic swirls chaotically.  You have
no sense of direction or location, and you can only hope you will
eventually land somewhere.
All of a sudden you feel your sense of reality returning, as the
vortex deposits you in an unfamiliar environment.
As you enter the vortex, all your weight seems to disappear.
You begin to accelerate at a seemingly impossible rate, right
into swirling colour and magic.

10.name: A Shimmering Maze ?
desc: "   You stand in a strange, magical maze.  Vertical shimmering walls
and a black obsidian floor restrict your movement.  High above a
strange green star shines eerily down upon you.  Strange howling
noises and shrieks reverberate through this maze, origin unknown.

desc: "   You stand in a strange, magical maze.  Vertical shimmering walls
and a black obsidian floor restrict your movement.  High above a
strange green star shines eerily down upon you.  Strange howling
noises and shrieks reverberate through this maze, origin unknown.

120.name: Top of the Tower
desc: "   You stand before a wooden door, at the very top of this
mysterious tower.  A small window sits in the wall here, viewing
the outside world.
"   Looking out the window, you can see the vast expanse of this
maze.  It stretches for as far as you can see, bathed in an
bizarre green light.  A large variety of monsters can be seen
prowling the maze, fighting amongst themselves.

121.name: The Mazemaster's Abode
desc: "   You stand in a large room at the top of the tower.  All around
you are vast windows, through which you can see a large maze,
stretching for miles and miles in all directions.  Several
telescopic devices sit on tripods, and a large desk with notebooks
sits in the middle.

300.name: A large meeting room
desc: "   You stand in a large, circular, marble-walled room.  Up above you a very
fashionable and delicate crystal sky-light floods the room with a bright sunny
light.  Towards the North, over-hanging a small archway sits the head of a
creature, two magnificent horns protruding from each side of it's head.  Under-
-neath this is a plaque with 'MaKaG' enscribed upon it.  A large oaken table
sits to the western side of this hall.  Exits lead to the North, through a small
archway; West into what appears to be a common room; East leads into a small
reception area and South leads to the entrance of the guild.

301.name: The Guildmaster's office
desc: "   A small room surrounds you here.  It's low-ceiling and plush carpet ensure
a feeling of cosiness is instilled in all who come here.  A polished wooden
desk sits at the northern end of the room, covered in stacks of scrolls and
other official looking books.  A large picture behind the desk depicts a
ranting Moose, streaking through a storm.  Dusty bookcases line the walls to
the East and West, packed with tomes.  Your only way out is through an archway
to the South.

350.name: An Art Gallery
desc: "   You have stepped into an Art Gallery of some description.  A long corridor
stretches out before you, its walls lined with strange glyphical artworks.

390.name: The Bottom end of the Slippery Slide

399.name: The Gift Shop
desc: "   You have entered a gift shop in the art gallery.  Prints of various artists'
works are available here for reasonable prices.  A super-slippery-slide is
located in the corner, for those wishing a speedy return to the market plaza.
A warning sign posted at the slide reads:
This slide hurts!  Use at own risk!

445.name: Some kind of lust-filled domicile
desc: "   Here forbidden couples couple.  All around the room strange
objects litter the floor, straps hang from the ceiling and
manacles from the walls.  A large cabinet stands to one side
while an emperor-sized bed is plonked right in centre of the
room.  Silk sheets glisten in the soft moon-light that filters
through the light curtains, which themselves seem to float on
the warm breeze that flows from outside.  Plush cushions sit
in every corner, and lie about the floor.  A very plush carpet
can be felt underfoot, sinking an inch beneath you.  Truely
this is a room for comfort and pleasure.

500.name: Cooper's Bar
desc: "  You find yourself in a dark, smoke-filled bar.  Some kind of
weirdo stands behind the bar, tending drinks for various patrons.
His name tag reads, in almost illegible writing, "Cooper".
Around the bar are various bar-like items.  A pool table, where
some Pizza delivery boys are having an argument.  A flashing, noisy
pinball machine, depicting some famous movie.  Finally there are
several tables and chairs, empty for now.
Cooper pokes you in the ribs and asks you if you want a drink or
whether you would like to just fuck off someplace else instead.

501.name: Tsudo's Stupid Arena
desc: "   This strange conflaguration is designed to cause as much blood to
spill as possible, in the shortest time possible.  So stand tall and
gut each other senseless!

desc: "   This strange conflaguration is designed to cause as much blood to
spill as possible, in the shortest time possible.  So stand tall and
gut each other senseless!

506.name: Falling off the arena
desc: "   This strange conflaguration is designed to cause as much blood to

gut each other senseless!

948.name: The Vault
desc: "   You now stand within the lich's treasure vault, a huge treasure
lies in the center of the room. The room is decorated with many marble
columns, in the far corner you can make out a shiimering portal........
through which you can see a path along a vast mountain range.

949.name: A Jar of Pickles
desc: "   Gigantic green gherkins float with you inside this glass chamber.  Rough,
slimy skins brush up against you, nudging you this way and that through a hazy
yellow fluid.  You feel quite pickled yourself, as you breathe this sour
solution into your lungs.  Gulping as would a Goldfish.  You can only catch
fleeting glimpses of the glass boundaries here - quick peeks at the real world
running about outside.  Someday a kind stranger might take a fancy to you and
rescue you from this suspended horror.

950.name: A large yellow bus-stop
desc: "   An old-fashioned bus-stop stands here, in the eternal wait for a bus.
Bits of green chewing gum adorn the crumbling wooden seat, and some
strange glyphical writing in purple and green mar the metal framework.
[]      C-C-C-C-C-C-C-C-W-W-W-W                                              []
[]      C | CASTLE  | C N N   W                                              []
[]  W-A-C-C-C-C-C-C-C-C   N-# W-W                                            []
[]  W-W   O-O   M-A-A-G-G-G R-A-W                                            []
[]    W-T O-O-O-M     G # G R   W                                            []
[]    W T # S-S-M-S-S G-G-G R   W                                            []
[]    W T-# S   M-# S   #   R   W                                            []
[]    W-L-L-L-L-M-L-L-L-L-L-L-L W                                            []
[]    W #-S-S   M     S-S A   L-W                                            []
[]    W-S-S-S-S-M   #-S   A-W-W-W                                            []
[]    W A-A     M-S-S-S   A                                                  []
[]    W-W-W-W-W-M-W-W-W-W-W                                                  []

953.name: Falling into the Fiery Depths of Hell

954.name: Falling into the Fiery Depths of Hell

955.name: Tsudo's Hair Salon
desc: "   This is the salon that the upper echelons of society, with all their money
and fancy baubles, avoid like the plague.  Grimy, dirty and generally not
nice, this salon could easily be mistaken for a seedy downtown strip club.
Naturally one might even propose that it is a strip club, given the naked
women prancing about here and there, the bar and the jukebox.  Tsudo insists
however, that these facilities are merely for those bored waiting for their
hair to be attended to.  Whatever the case, it can be argued that it is
indeed possible to have one's hair cut and styled here if one so desired.
Thus it remains named so, Tsudo's Hair Salon.

980.name: DEATH TRAP :)
980.desc: Room to purge my mobs coz I dont have purge :)

981.name: A fading trail
desc: "   Through this thick foliage you can spot a very faint trail of
broken branches.  Here and there spots of dark red blood can be seen
on the leaves and grasses.  The trail leads north.

982.name: A trail through the hills
desc: "   The trail here is quite clear, leading up through some low rolling
hills.  You can see some strange footprints along here, very large and
quite deep.  To the south is a dense forest of foliage, a faint trail
is visible through it.

983.name: A valley ahead
desc: "   You are surrounded by rolling hills, the trail here is quite
well-used, and could almost be called a road.  To the north you
can spot a very dark valley, the trail appears to lead straight
into the mouth of this valley.  To the south you can see
the trail running across some hills and down into a dense cover
of bushlands.

984.name: The hidden Gully
desc: "   You stand in a dark Gully, a small muddy brown stream runs
past you to the East and steep earthen cliffs to the West.
Ahead you can spot some sort of structure hidden in the darkness.

985.name: Before a large steel prison
desc: "   You stand before a large cubic steel prison block.  A glow can be
seen surrounding the dull grey walls.  The gully here is dark and
dank, your only exit south towards the light.

990.name: A small potato crisp on an sea of vinegar.

997.name: The smoko room.
desc: "   You are assaulted with a combination of pornography and thick grey
smoke, not exactly a go-able pair, but a strange enough sensation in any
case.  A large centerfold of 1966 Playboy pet of the year sternly looks
you over as you find a place to sit and smoke your lungs out.  Here and
there you hear the hacking and spluttering of those smokers who simply
can't handle the pressure of large fleshy objects watching them puff.
As you reach into your pocket and pull out a cigarette you wonder how
severe your toxic shock would be if you tried to smoke the nicotine
infected posters.

998.name: The Master Bedroom
desc: "   Tsudo has a really big bed, he must be rich.  A 4poster bed stands in
the centre of the room, with silk sheets and a hot water bottle on top.
A picture of Opella sits on a bedside table, obviously Tsudo anticipates
her arrival to the upper planes.

999.name: Tsudo's Joint.
desc: "   You have entered a study.  A large wooden desk stands in the centre,
riddled with pen marks and scratches.  A big cushy chair with dust along
the top and cigarette burns in the arms is behind the desk.  To the left is
a large dark fire place, crackling away.  The wood veneer walls are covered
with tattered posters of mythical beasts and adventurers.  An eerie smoke
fills the room, smelling faintly of tobacco, but with something else mixed
in.  A small sure-footed figure in black melts out of the shadows and asks,
"Got a smoke guvna?".
Tsudo stuffs his hand into a secret pocket in his black life jacket and pulls
out a pack of smokes.  He flips the lid, pushes a cigarette out and taps
the end of it on the desk.  He puts the pack back into his life jacket and
fumbles around for a lighter.  Finding one in his shirt pocket, he puts
on a concentrated frown and covers the flame with one hand while puffing on
the cigarette with the other.  Satisfied that the cigarette is lit he
breaths back a large amount of smoke, before going cross-eyed and coughing
and spluttering all over the place.  A few moments later he recovers and
beams you a big evil grin.
"   The figure is none other than the remarkable ninja Tsudo!
His evil gleam suggests that tsudo likes to be a pain in the bum..
You might want to get out of the way, you think you see flows of power
forming in his mind...
Your limbs are frozen in place!
